inglePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2527385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Mai 15, 2026</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104exv1665702549479.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exv1665702549479.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/exv1665702549479.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"exv1665702549479\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      /ini\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Specify the initialization file or GUI resource file used by the application.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exv1665702549479__section_w2437ab1b5b1_w2438ab1b5_w2439ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149732e1_d149733e1_d149734e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini=</code>{<var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var>}<var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exv1665702549479__section_w2440ab1b5b3_w2441ab1b5_w2442ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d368399e66\">\n                  \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149738e1_d149739e1_d149740e1\">Run the application using the initialization file <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149741e1_d149742e1_d149743e1\">The path to, and name of, the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file is determined according to the following rules:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52085e1_d52086e1_d52087e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149744e1_d149745e1_d149746e1\">If <var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var> is omitted, the\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ini</span> switch should be preceded by the\n                     <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/adm</span> switch to specify the directory where the application's\n                  configuration files are located.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52088e1_d52089e1_d52090e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149747e1_d149748e1_d149749e1\">If the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ini</span> switch is present and is immediately followed by an equals sign (=), the following string is presumed to contain the path to, and name of, the <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span> file to be used.</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52091e1_d52092e1_d52093e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149750e1_d149751e1_d149752e1\">If you specify a <var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var>, enter the complete path, not a relative path. For example:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149753e1_d149754e1_d149755e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini=d:uni/xyz/test.ini</code>\n                        not\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini=../xyz/test.ini</code>\n</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149756e1_d149757e1_d149758e1\">If you do not specify a <var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var>, Uniface searches for <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span> directory.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52094e1_d52095e1_d52096e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149759e1_d149760e1_d149761e1\">If you do not specify an extension for <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var>, it is presumed to be <span class=\"ph filepath\">.ini</span>.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52097e1_d52098e1_d52099e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149762e1_d149763e1_d149764e1\">Do not use spaces around the equals sign (=). For example:</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149765e1_d149766e1_d149767e1\">\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini=test.ini</code>\n                        not\n                        <code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini = test.ini</code>\n</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52100e1_d52101e1_d52102e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149768e1_d149769e1_d149770e1\">If no equals sign (=) is present (with or without a text string), an error message is returned to indicate that the <code class=\"ph codeph\">/ini</code> switch is incorrect.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"exv1665702549479__li_d52103e1_d52104e1_d52105e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149771e1_d149772e1_d149773e1\">If no <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">/ini</span> switch is specified, <var class=\"keyword varname\">FileName</var> is presumed to be <span class=\"ph filepath\">usys.ini</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span> directory.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149774e1_d149775e1_d149776e1\">In all cases, <var class=\"keyword varname\">Path</var> is presumed to be <span class=\"ph filepath\">$USYSADM</span> (<span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span>).</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"exv1665702549479__section_w2443ab1b5b5_w2444ab1b5_w2445ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d368399e213\">Example: Using /ini </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149780e1_d149781e1_d149782e1\">In the following example, assignments are located in a file named <span class=\"ph filepath\">myapp.ini</span> in the default <span class=\"ph filepath\">/adm</span> subdirectory under the Uniface installation directory:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/ini=myapp</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"exv1665702549479__p_d149783e1_d149784e1_d149785e1\">In the following example, assignments are located in a file named <span class=\"ph filepath\">testmyapp.ini</span> in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/testadm</span> subdirectory under the Uniface installation directory:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">/ini=d:uniface/testadm/testmyapp.ini</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eiq1665702549359.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/adm</a><p>Specify the directory where the application's configuration files are located.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/iil1665702549278.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>/asn</a><p>Specify the assignment file used by the application.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sjo1665702919851.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Uniface Files and Executables</a><p>During installation, a large number of files and executables are installed. Some of the most important are described in the topics in this section.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/asd1665702742243.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configuration Files</a><p>Uniface configuration files include assignment files, initialization files, and web application files.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527385\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "/ini Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Mai 15, 2026 Summarize Uniface 10.4 /ini Specify the initialization file or GUI resource file used by the application. /ini= { Path } FileName Description Run the application using the initialization file FileName . The path to, and name of, the .ini file is determined according to the following rules: If Path is omitted, the /ini switch should be preceded by the /adm switch to specify the directory where the application's configuration files are located. If the /ini switch is present and is immediately followed by an equals sign (=), the following string is presumed to contain the path to, and name of, the .ini file to be used. If you specify a Path , enter the complete path, not a relative path. For example: /ini=d:uni/xyz/test.ini not /ini=../xyz/test.ini If you do not specify a Path , Uniface searches for FileName in the /adm directory. If you do not specify an extension for FileName , it is presumed to be .ini . Do not use spaces around the equals sign (=). For example: /ini=test.ini not /ini = test.ini If no equals sign (=) is present (with or without a text string), an error message is returned to indicate that the /ini switch is incorrect. If no /ini switch is specified, FileName is presumed to be usys.ini in the /adm directory. In all cases, Path is presumed to be $USYSADM ( /adm ). Example: Using /ini In the following example, assignments are located in a file named myapp.ini in the default /adm subdirectory under the Uniface installation directory: /ini=myapp Copy In the following example, assignments are located in a file named testmyapp.ini in the /testadm subdirectory under the Uniface installation directory: /ini=d:uniface/testadm/testmyapp.ini Copy Related Links /adm Specify the directory where the application's configuration files are located. /asn Specify the assignment file used by the application. Uniface Files and Executables During installation, a large number of files and executables are installed. Some of the most important are described in the topics in this section. Configuration Files Uniface configuration files include assignment files, initialization files, and web application files. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}